## Known Technical Debt

- `requireAuth()` in marketing CMS bypassed (hardcoded admin return) — temporary for staff access
- Marketing CMS middleware excludes `/api/upload` from auth — intentional for hub proxy
- All Mind Measure repos auto-deploy on push to `main` — verified via Vercel deployment `source=git` history. The old exceptions for pro hub, university hub, and docs site have been resolved (pro hub Vercel link was repaired May 2026 after the underlying GitHub repo transfer to the `Mind-Measure` org).
- Mobile apps need push notifications (roadmap item)
- Shared packages (`@mindmeasure/*`) need version management attention
- **Cost-monitoring dashboard broken end-to-end** (Pro and likely Uni) — `cost_tracking`, `cost_budgets`, `cost_alerts` tables don't exist on Aurora. Migration files exist (`mind-measure-pro-core/migrations/020_cost_tracking.sql` is Aurora-clean; legacy `cost-tracking-schema.sql` for budgets/alerts still has Supabase `auth.users` FKs and needs cleaning) but no admin runner endpoints, so nothing ever ran. Even after creating tables, no cost-tracking writes are happening from ElevenLabs / Bedrock / Rekognition calls, so dashboard would show zeros. Full fix = ~half a day: migration + runner, verify write path, ElevenLabs/Bedrock backfill. Currently surfaces as 500s from `/api/database/select` when superuser opens the Cost Monitoring tab — contained, no other features affected. Deferred May 2026 — pick up when there's appetite for unit economics view.

